description: An eerie calm settles over the destruction wrought by the god Susano. The mystic dharmaquation has gone awry, boding ill for the future of the Yamata Empire and all those on the planet! Susano and his summoner, Fuzen, set out to investigate, while Fuzen's daughter, Seska, begins a quest for power. Her exposure to the mystic equation has left her changed -- and a focus for all the negative karma of the entire Empire!

The powerful god Susano fights the Eight Wizards from Hell and the might of the Empire while Seska visits the mystic library world to find the scroll that may give a chance of controlling him. All the fighting is an attempt to stall for time so Dr. Hebime can set off the Naga-Reactor that will incinerate all the evil Karma in the Empire! But only Susano knows that the magical Dharmaquation is incorrect, and its use threatens the fundamental nature of existence itself! For all his efforts, Susano is too late, as Princess Kushinata sacrifices herself in the core of the Naga-Reactor!

The Naga-reactor has been triggered, and is rapidly growing out of control. Designed to absorb the negative karma of the entire empire, it has manifested in the form of a nine-headed dragon, growing so large it threatens to destroy the planet! As Commander Ronnell defends the emperor and Dr. Hebime attempts to take control of the reactor, the dragon grows and grows... Seska, now under the influence of the malevolent tenth element, attempts to take control of the empire herself! It's up to the god Susano and Seska's father Fuzen to make her see reason, but what can be done when she refuses to recognize her father, and swats Susano into the moon?!
The final battle to decide of the fate of universe is here. Who lives? Who dies? The answers are here.

description: You can't have a perfect society without perfect people, and the only perfect people are the ones you can manufacture. The governing body of Olympus is about to bring utopia crashing down around their ears as they seek to regulate the minds and bodies of the human race or fully replace them with plastic substitutes. Deunan and Bri, still new to the city, find themselves in the unlikely position of having to hold together this house of cards. Their strategy? Destroy the old foundation and pray everything stands while the new roots develop!In this second Appleseed volume Deunan and Bri become fully integrated into Olympus society, even as they seek to turn it on its ear. Spectacular art and an exciting story set Appleseed apart as an example of comics at its finest.
name: Prometheus Unbound

description: A renegade, flesh-eating bioroid (enhanced artificial human) is stalking the ruins of Manhattan, and Olympus' elite ESWAT is sent in to take her down! Will Deunan and Bri emerge as heroes, or as lunch meat? It's a dangerous world outside Olympus, and things aren't exactly rosey within its utopian walls! This third volume is the most action-filled yet, pitting the duo against AWOL laboratory monsters and fanatical terrorists! But in all the action, master manga creator Masamune Shirow still manages to find time to explore the summits and valleys of a relationship between a young woman and her overprotective cyborg companion. Open your eyes to Appleseed: it's sexy, exciting, and always entertaining!
name: The Scales of Prometheus

description: Dark Horse starts its regular publication schedule of manga collections with a bang! Masamune Shirow's acclaimed cyberpunk epic about ESWAT operative Deunan and her robot lover Briareos continues its successful run with a fourth collection -- but now it's at Dark Horse. Beautiful art and a complex and fully realized future world make this among the best of the manga titles available in the United States.
name: The Promethean Balance

description: A light-hearted police comedy set in a future where the norms are vast bio-constructed cities, air so foul that citizens must wear masks outside, and a police department that includes a crack tank-squad. Join Leona, her pet tank Bonaparte, and her lovesick partner Al as they confront the villainous Buaku and his felinoid accessories-to-crime-- the beautiful Annapuma and Unipuma. Leona's goal: to rescue Crolis, a mysterious green-skinned girl with the power to cleanse the air around her, and the potential to renew the poisoned earth. This book collects all six issues of the popular series originally published by Eclipse Books.
name: Collected Edition

description:
Overview
Leona Ozaki is the most experienced tank patrol cop in Newport City's Police Department. She's faced down gun-toting sky pirates and berserk street thugs and walked away with hardly a scratch! But not even her battle experience could have prepared her for the adversaries awaiting her back at HQ -- the love-starved, female cops who want to keep her away from heartthrob police chief Sakurai! On top of that, Leona has to contend with her new law-enforcement partner, Annapuma, a woman who can't figure out the difference between being chased by the police and wearing the badge herself!

Overview
It's a workday from hell for officer Leona Ozaki. The jealous traffic-meter girls are determined to get between her and handsome chief-of-staff Sakura; her uptight subordinate Shinozaki has mysteriously disappeared into the Traffic Control Division; and sky pirate Urushi-Maru is flying free above the city. Leona has neither the time nor the patience for this -- but what she does have are three HEAT rounds, and if she aims them just right she can end all of her troubles!

Overview
The flipped red flag of an expired parking meter is the favored sight of Newport's intrepid meter maids! Or, rather, it was the favored sight, before studly chief-of-staff Sakura came to the Newport Police Department! So when tank policewoman Leona Ozaki appears to be making time with the handsome superintendent, the maids take to the streets to put an end to the pairing . . . and find themselves in the middle of a raging gang brawl!

Overview
Leona's tank is state of the art! It can go over, under, or through any obstacle -- or, rather, any obstacle besides a crowd of anti-Tank Police peaceniks! When the only thing standing between your outrageous firepower and the biggest bust of your life is a pack of demonstrating pacifists, what do you do?

Overview
Bringing infamous sky pirate Urushi-Maru down to earth was no problem. Pump enough Sayori-14 HEAT rounds into a biplane, it's not gonna stay up for long. But the real battle still lies ahead for tank-cop Leona Ozaki; now she has to explain to her supervising officer why one of the city's most important factories is going up in smoke! Leona may always get her man, but they sure don't come along easily!

Intron Depot 2: Blades is the newest full-color book from creator Masamune Shirow (Appleseed and Ghost in the Shell). It collects 209 fantasy-themed illustrations, paintings, and computer graphics created by Shirow between 1992 and May 1998, none of which have been published in the U.S. before. It also contains detailed commentary (in both Japanese and English) on each work, and an "info-box" that explains the techniques used to produce each piece.

112 pages
name: Blades

description:
Ballistics features a treasure trove of spectacular full-color illustrations featuring high-caliber treatments. Often a sci-fi military theme is evoked, with special emphasis on detailed weaponry, but there is also a healthy batch of fantasy themes and outer space action. In addition to his traditional drawing and painting expertise, Shirow is also one of the foremost talents in computer graphics. Not only does he create exceptionally realistic backgrounds and vehicles, but in this volume presents alternate "takes" on the main image, presenting different color combinations, daytime/nightime versions and other variations on the primary theme.

128 pages
name: Ballistics

description: A battered and bleeding man seeks out water to rest and heal. He is Tor, and he has been brutally beaten and exiled from his tribe. Resting, he eats fruit that may be psychoactive. He dreams about his past and the fearsome world around him, and ponders the night sky. He travels far overland, and eventually comes across an infant tied to the rock in a nearby pool. The infant is unlike any he's seen before - it's hairy and odd looking. Just then a crocodilian beast surfaces, and Tor jumps forward to the rescue... but that's when his troubles really begin!
name: The Outcast
